on Cenancle Island before,

257
00:14:23,125 --> 00:14:24,833
and I think the authorities
are pretty clueless

258
00:14:24,916 --> 00:14:26,041
as to what caused it.

259
00:14:26,125 --> 00:14:27,583
[BOY 5A]
Mommy, I'm tired!

260
00:14:27,666 --> 00:14:30,083
Can we go home? Pretty please!

261
00:14:30,166 --> 00:14:32,291
I wish we could, but
with the buses not running,

262
00:14:32,375 --> 00:14:34,208
there's nothing I can do!

263
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:35,750
Sorry to ask,
but do you mind if we

264
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,166
take a little detour?

265
00:14:37,250 --> 00:14:38,958
Of course! Go right ahead!

266
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:41,833
[laughing]

267
00:14:41,916 --> 00:14:43,791
I can't help myself;
it's just my nature.

268
00:14:43,875 --> 00:14:45,000
You know what I mean?

269
00:14:45,083 --> 00:14:48,000
Well, in my opinion,
it's a wonderful thing!

270
00:14:48,083 --> 00:14:50,250
Thanks for escorting
us home, sir!

271
00:14:50,333 --> 00:14:52,750
It was really nice
to meet you, Miss!

272
00:14:56,333 --> 00:14:57,750
See? It's my nature!

273
00:14:57,833 --> 00:14:59,416
I just can't help myself!

274
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:00,291
Right!

275
00:15:00,375 --> 00:15:01,916
We haven't even formally met.

276
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,583
Forgive my manners. I'm Robert.

277
00:15:03,666 --> 00:15:04,958
What's your name?

278
00:15:05,041 --> 00:15:06,541
I'm Nene Nanakorobi.

279
00:15:06,625 --> 00:15:08,333
And this is my friend, Cla-ring.

280
00:15:08,416 --> 00:15:09,916
Clarion.

281
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,125
[ALTMAN]
All right.

282
00:15:11,208 --> 00:15:13,416
Nice to meet you,
Nene. Cla-ring.

283
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:16,208
[NENE] It's nice to
meet you too, Robert!

284
00:15:16,291 --> 00:15:18,291
[CLARION]
Clarion.

285
00:15:18,375 --> 00:15:21,125
[ALTMAN]
Sorry again! I can't help it.

286
00:15:21,208 --> 00:15:24,333
Honestly, I didn't mean to
take us this far out of the way.

287
00:15:24,416 --> 00:15:25,250
Whoops.

288
00:15:25,333 --> 00:15:26,291
[NENE]
Oh, that's all right.

289
00:15:26,375 --> 00:15:28,083
It was nice to
help others in need.

290
00:15:28,166 --> 00:15:30,625
[OLD LADY 5A yelling]

291
00:15:30,708 --> 00:15:33,083
These bots are like
sitting ducks out here!

292
00:15:33,166 --> 00:15:34,333
[TSUKASA]
Oh yeah!

293
00:15:34,416 --> 00:15:36,250
This is one of Pony's rarest,
high-end models.

294
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:37,750
We're gonna be
filthy rich, dude!

295
00:15:37,833 --> 00:15:38,875
They took Mii!

296
00:15:38,958 --> 00:15:40,958
Please! Help me get her back!

297
00:15:41,041 --> 00:15:42,250
Are you all right, Ma'am?

298
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:43,083
You have to help!

299
00:15:43,166 --> 00:15:45,250
My Mii is like family to me!

300
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:48,250
Nene! You look after her!

301
00:15:48,333 --> 00:15:50,125
No! I'll go, too!

302
00:15:53,750 --> 00:15:54,958
[NENE]
Cla-ring!

303
00:15:56,416 --> 00:15:57,916
[ALTMAN]
What was that?

304
00:16:00,500 --> 00:16:03,000
Dude... What the hell?
My freakin' loot vanished?

305
00:16:03,083 --> 00:16:03,708
Me too.

306
00:16:03,791 --> 00:16:05,541
Damn! What was that?

307
00:16:05,625 --> 00:16:07,583
Check it out. A chick!

308
00:16:07,666 --> 00:16:09,041
Whoa. She's fast!

309
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:10,916
She took the bags
right out of our hands!

310
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,666
Loot recovery complete.

311
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:15,916
Dude, that's not a
chick; that's a robot!

312
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,041
It sure is.

313
00:16:17,125 --> 00:16:18,958
Come on, we should
steal that one, too!

314
00:16:19,041 --> 00:16:20,291
[CLARION growls]

315
00:16:20,375 --> 00:16:22,833
[TSUKASA] Okay, Bot, us
humans are in charge now.

316
00:16:22,916 --> 00:16:24,125
You better do what we say.

317
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:25,833
[CLARION]
Enemy threat confirmed.

318
00:16:25,916 --> 00:16:27,541
Switching to combat mode.

319
00:16:27,625 --> 00:16:28,666
Hold it!

320
00:16:29,583 --> 00:16:31,000
[ALTMAN]
You're not stealing a machine.

321
00:16:31,083 --> 00:16:33,166
You're kidnapping
someone's family member.

322
00:16:33,250 --> 00:16:35,125
Apologize to the lady
for what you've done,

323
00:16:35,208 --> 00:16:37,875
and I might let you
walk away from this!

324
00:16:37,958 --> 00:16:39,333
For real?

325
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:43,250
[KOTOBUKI] Save us the boring
lecture about right and wrong

326
00:16:43,333 --> 00:16:45,541
and hand over the
damn robot right now,

327
00:16:45,625 --> 00:16:47,333
or you'll be sorry, man!

328
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:49,500
[ALTMAN]
She's more than just a robot!

329
00:16:49,583 --> 00:16:51,541
Look at her. She's a girl!

330
00:16:52,833 --> 00:16:55,583
Oh, man.
This guy's crazy. Full-on!

331
00:16:55,666 --> 00:16:57,000
What can you do?

332
00:16:57,083 --> 00:17:00,750
And we just hate resorting
to violence so much!

333
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:02,000
Yes.

334
00:17:02,083 --> 00:17:03,875
I couldn't agree more.

335
00:17:03,958 --> 00:17:07,166
I was hoping we could settle
this peacefully, as well.

336
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:08,375
Uh oh.

337
00:17:08,458 --> 00:17:10,833
Is this guy just really
strong or somethin'?

338
00:17:10,916 --> 00:17:13,708
[NENE]
Claring! Robert!

339
00:17:16,208 --> 00:17:18,500
You have impeccable
timing, girly bot!

340
00:17:18,583 --> 00:17:19,625
[CLARION]
Nene!

341
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:22,541
[KOTOBUKI yells]

342
00:17:26,250 --> 00:17:28,250
[ALTMAN]
Hey. You guys all right?

343
00:17:28,333 --> 00:17:29,666
We're okay. Yes!

344
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:32,041
Mii! Thank you for
bringing her back to me!

345
00:17:32,125 --> 00:17:33,458
Glad I could help, ma'am.

346
00:17:33,541 --> 00:17:35,833
[laughing]

347
00:17:35,916 --> 00:17:37,458
[ALTMAN]
Sorry to hold up the show,

348
00:17:37,541 --> 00:17:40,000
but I gotta make sure these
guys get what they deserve.

349
00:17:40,083 --> 00:17:40,875
[NENE]
It's okay.

350
00:17:40,958 --> 00:17:43,208
We can make it home from here.

351
00:17:43,291 --> 00:17:46,083
It's just not in my nature
to let bad guys get away.

352
00:17:46,166 --> 00:17:49,041
Sorry for getting you and your
friend involved in this mess.

353
00:17:49,125 --> 00:17:51,166
No! Please don't apologize!

354
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:54,125
World peace is built
on things like this!

355
00:17:54,208 --> 00:17:55,916
[laughing]

356
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:57,500
World peace, huh?

357
00:17:57,583 --> 00:17:58,750
That's great!

358
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:01,375
I'll do my best to live
up to your expectations!

359
00:18:01,458 --> 00:18:02,250
Goodbye.

360
00:18:02,333 --> 00:18:03,791
You're a good egg, Nene.

361
00:18:03,875 --> 00:18:05,833
It's true. Cla-ring, too.

362
00:18:05,916 --> 00:18:06,958
Clarion.

363
00:18:08,958 --> 00:18:10,208
You know, Cla-ring...

364
00:18:10,291 --> 00:18:13,125
I think we did a lot to
achieve world peace today!

365
00:18:14,208 --> 00:18:16,208
What's wrong?

366
00:18:16,291 --> 00:18:17,500
It's Anna!

367
00:18:17,583 --> 00:18:19,833
What happened?
Are you all right?

368
00:18:21,875 --> 00:18:24,750
This is awful.
She needs a doctor!

369
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:27,875
I'll call an ambulance!

370
00:18:27,958 --> 00:18:29,375
There's no connection.

371
00:18:31,416 --> 00:18:33,416
[CLARION] If there is
something that you want to do,

372
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,583
just use the Pandora Device.

373
00:18:37,291 --> 00:18:40,250
Is it sneaky to use someone
else's power for good?

374
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:42,041
[NENE]
What?

375
00:18:42,125 --> 00:18:43,625
[CLARION]
Or is it just?

376
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:47,166
You're right. Anna's hurt.

377
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:50,375
Cla-ring? Come on. Let's help!

378
00:18:56,916 --> 00:18:59,291
[NENE]
Pandora Device. Open!

379
00:19:01,291 --> 00:19:05,666
[NENE] Decode skill.
Elpis Series! Paramedic!

380
00:19:08,208 --> 00:19:10,833
Don't worry, Anna,
you're in good hands now.

381
00:19:12,708 --> 00:19:14,250
[NENE]
Accessing prosthetic limb!

382
00:19:14,333 --> 00:19:15,666
Acquiring vital signs!

383
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:17,416
Reading clinical record!

384
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:18,625
I see it all!

385
00:19:18,708 --> 00:19:21,416
Her medical history.
Her drug history.

386
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:23,375
I know how to deal with this!

387
00:19:23,458 --> 00:19:25,541
This power may not be mine,

388
00:19:25,625 --> 00:19:28,125
but at least I can do
something good with it!

389
00:19:28,208 --> 00:19:29,833
She doesn't just
have a prosthetic limb.

390
00:19:29,916 --> 00:19:32,416
She's also using artificial
internal organs.

391
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:33,750
Since she's not cyberized,

392
00:19:33,833 --> 00:19:35,333
they're monitored
via the network.

393
00:19:35,416 --> 00:19:37,625
That's why the
disturbance led to errors!

394
00:19:40,958 --> 00:19:42,666
[NENE]
Pinpoint the symptoms!

395
00:19:47,208 --> 00:19:48,875
If I take over
control of your system,

396
00:19:48,958 --> 00:19:50,625
then it'll buy us time.

397
00:19:50,708 --> 00:19:53,250
But we've got to get you
to a hospital right away!

398
00:19:53,333 --> 00:19:56,250
Nene. We need a ride.

399
00:19:56,333 --> 00:19:57,958
Luckily, we have one.

400
00:19:58,041 --> 00:20:00,333
Show yourselves now,
Gertsecommas!

401
00:20:02,083 --> 00:20:03,125
[NENE gasps]

402
00:20:03,208 --> 00:20:04,791
They were concealed
using Takumi's

403
00:20:04,875 --> 00:20:06,916
thermo-optical camouflage.

404
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,000
Thank goodness they're here!

405
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:12,500
We'll be there
in no time, Anna.

406
00:20:12,583 --> 00:20:13,916
Hang in there!

407
00:20:19,916 --> 00:20:22,000
[TOTO] Well...
There's no need to worry now.

408
00:20:22,083 --> 00:20:24,375
But it's a good thing
you got here when you did.

409
00:20:24,458 --> 00:20:25,958
Thank you so much, Nene.

410
00:20:26,041 --> 00:20:27,166
You saved my life.

411
00:20:27,250 --> 00:20:28,041
Of course.

412
00:20:28,125 --> 00:20:29,625
I'm just glad you're okay now.

413
00:20:29,708 --> 00:20:32,208
You weren't hurt lifting
me off the ground, were you?

414
00:20:32,291 --> 00:20:33,666
Are you kidding?

415
00:20:33,750 --> 00:20:36,125
I'm a full-bodied cyborg,
so it didn't faze me at all.

416
00:20:36,208 --> 00:20:38,375
[ANNA gasps]

417
00:20:38,458 --> 00:20:40,958
[ANNA]
My, my. A full-bodied cyborg.

418
00:20:41,041 --> 00:20:44,500
I've heard rumors of your kind.

419
00:20:44,583 --> 00:20:47,750
That's wonderful.
Good for you, Nene.

420
00:20:47,833 --> 00:20:50,291
Uh... thank you?

421
00:20:50,375 --> 00:20:51,708
[ANNOUNCER 5A]
Please be advised.

422
00:20:51,791 --> 00:20:54,333
The network disturbance
has officially been resolved.

423
00:20:54,416 --> 00:20:57,625
I repeat: The network
disturbance has officially be--

424
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:04,541
Good for you, Nene.

425
00:21:04,625 --> 00:21:05,750
Anna praised me.

426
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:07,416
That's never happened before.

427
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:13,416
[NENE] Although...
I did have a little help.

428
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:15,791
[phone ringing]

429
00:21:15,875 --> 00:21:16,791
Nene here.

430
00:21:16,875 --> 00:21:18,666
[TAKUMI]
Nene! Are you okay?

431
00:21:18,750 --> 00:21:20,458
Nothing's happened to you, yeah?

432
00:21:20,541 --> 00:21:23,083
I'm fine.
No need to be worried!

433
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:30,083
[ALTMAN]
Pardon me, sir.

434
00:21:30,166 --> 00:21:32,208
Captain Robert Altman reporting.

435
00:21:33,958 --> 00:21:35,625
[ALTMAN]
Special Military Adviser Kurtz.

436
00:21:35,708 --> 00:21:38,916
What is it can I do
to assist you, sir?

437
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,333
[KURTZ]
You're late.

438
00:21:40,416 --> 00:21:43,291
It's 42 seconds past the
appointed time, Captain Altman.

439
00:21:43,375 --> 00:21:45,375
[ALTMAN]
I apologize, sir.

440
00:21:45,458 --> 00:21:47,666
The sudden network disturbance
resulted in disorder

441
00:21:47,750 --> 00:21:49,875
all across the island,
as you know.

442
00:21:49,958 --> 00:21:52,333
Life is time, Captain,
and nothing more.

443
00:21:52,416 --> 00:21:53,916
Don't waste mine.

444
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:58,041
Making light of time is
something only savages do.

445
00:21:58,125 --> 00:21:59,958
I will remember that, sir.

446
00:22:04,583 --> 00:22:06,375
I am requisitioning
four of your force's

447
00:22:06,458 --> 00:22:08,708
underwater duty robots, Captain.

448
00:22:08,791 --> 00:22:10,208
Get them ready.

449
00:22:10,291 --> 00:22:12,166
Four? But sir...

450
00:22:12,250 --> 00:22:14,125
Is that necessary?

451
00:22:14,208 --> 00:22:15,541
Forgive me.

452
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:17,833
Not to speak out of turn,
but we just gave you six.

453
00:22:17,916 --> 00:22:20,208
[KURTZ]
They were lost.

454
00:22:20,291 --> 00:22:21,500
And why do you need them?

455
00:22:21,583 --> 00:22:23,833
I don't feel
inclined to explain.

456
00:22:23,916 --> 00:22:25,416
You have your orders, Captain.

457
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:27,333
I want them by tomorrow.

458
00:22:27,416 --> 00:22:28,541
[ALTMAN]
Yes, sir.

459
00:22:28,625 --> 00:22:30,875
I will have them ready
for you before noon.

460
00:22:30,958 --> 00:22:32,458
[KURTZ]
One other thing.

461
00:22:32,541 --> 00:22:34,750
I want you to be sure to
carry out that other order

462
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:37,000
regarding Vulcan Harbor Park.

463
00:22:37,083 --> 00:22:39,166
You can count on me, sir.

464
00:22:39,250 --> 00:22:42,083
And remember: it's all
for the sake of world peace.

465
00:22:48,166 --> 00:22:50,791
[ALTMAN]
Nene. Cla-ring.

466
00:22:50,875 --> 00:22:52,666
There might be peace coming.

467
00:22:52,750 --> 00:22:54,750
But I'm afraid it's
going to be much different

468
00:22:54,833 --> 00:22:56,333
than you imagined.

469
00:23:28,875 --> 00:23:30,166
We really need to play doctor,

470
00:23:30,250 --> 00:23:31,916
'cause I am dying to see you
dressed up like a nurse!

471
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,000
That is pointless.

472
00:23:33,083 --> 00:23:34,625
Just use the
Pandora Device, Nene.

473
00:23:34,708 --> 00:23:36,166
Wait! Maybe I should
dress up like a nurse

474
00:23:36,250 --> 00:23:38,375
and you can be my patient
and I'll take care of you!

475
00:23:38,458 --> 00:23:40,625
I think she might
need to go to a hospital.

476
00:24:30,125 --> 00:24:31,416
[NENE]
Robert! You know what?

477
00:24:31,500 --> 00:24:33,458
You're what they call
a champion of justice!

478
00:24:33,541 --> 00:24:35,958
[ALTMAN laughs]
It's my nature!

479
00:24:36,041 --> 00:24:37,125
[NENE]
I respect you!

480
00:24:37,208 --> 00:24:38,375
[CLARION]
Nene.

481
00:24:38,458 --> 00:24:41,041
Takumi told you to stop
fixating on older men.

